A great port from 3DS to Mobile Phone, bringing all the good aspects of the original game but with lots of cutting Let's be frank. You CAN NOT play it offline, your phone have to be connected to the Internet which sucks when youre on airplane mode or the connection is unstable. The worst part is the late game content is incomplete: you may not hatch the DLC Elder dragon/monsties such as Kushala, Teo, and Rajang. You are stuck with only Silver & Gold Rath as your final late game monsties.

This game was originally a Nintendo 3ds game that was a spinoff of the Monster Hunter series of games. However, even though this game is a spinoff, no prior knowledge of the franchise is required to fully experience this game. With this mobile port of the game comes many improvements over the 3ds version like improved render distance and framerate. Overall I'd recommend this to anyone who likes turn based RPGs such as Pokemon or Dragon Quest or anyone who likes Monster Hunter.

This is a truly great RPG for mobile. Excellent port from a DS game, it has great optimization (provided you have the recommended hardware) and the graphics are great for a mobile game. Gameplay is also great, very easy to get into. The world is expansive with a lot of things to explore, but it's quite linear as you need to progress in the story to access new areas. The downside for me is the always connected DRM, if you don't have a stable internet connection you can't play the game. Wish they could remove that. Also, haven't been able to do network battles as it be bug or something. Just couldn't get it to work for PVP. Still would recommend this game for anyone looking to play a new RPG.

I had to take a moment to leave a review for this game. I'm an avid mobile gamer and am very picky when it comes to finding a game I want to invest my time in to, which is why I was so excited when I found this gem. I was skeptic of the $20 price-tag at first, but after diving in to the game my doubts quickly vanished. I've played over 16 hours in just 3 days. It's hard to put down. I'm not even a quarter of the way through the game according to my progress log and already feel l've gotten my money's worth. The graphics and audio are beautiful; well above-average compared to most other mobile RPGs. The story is heartfelt, engaging, and has kept my interest. I typically favor the combat-style fighting of MMOs, but the turn-based battle system of this game is surprisingly refreshing, dynamic, and challenging (in a good way). That and the monster collection and training aspects of this game are very reminiscent of the Pokemon games, for any fans of the series. I have yet to encounter bugs or glitches of any sort. Overall, I'd say this is easily one of the best mobile RPGs I've played to-date, and I've played MANY. There's really not much room for improvement. I'm happy I picked it up!

This game is fun and addicting as well as cute and colorful. It's not like other Monster Hunter games, but more like a monster collection battle RPG (with simple rock, paper, scissors style combat) that is Monster Hunter themed! It's great for me and how I play it (only using it and no other apps/mobile features at the same time on a plugged in device), but I could see it being an issue for some people as it kills battery and tends to crash if you multitask apps while playing it. Note: It cannot currently be played offline AND remember to save frequently! It does autosave but it may not autosave as frequently as you want, to save rest at your house and select save or use a catavan stand/cat to save. Also Note: This version of the game doesn't have all the additional content that the Japanese version has.

I could gush about how wonderful this is, but I'll keep it simple. This is the best game available for mobile right now. Its 3DS incarnation is what ruined other turn-based RPGs for me- and for the right reasons. Try the demo if you must, but know that in owning smartphones for over a decade, this is the only mobile game I've put more than twenty hours into, and yet still get home from work or wake up on my days off ACTIVELY EXCITED about playing more. For the tech boys: Using a Sony Xperia XZ Premium: only the occasional crash to report, alongside a few issues with sound effects going missing seemingly due to using battle speed-up. The new autosave feature largely mitigated the first issue (awesome), and the second only required reopening the app, which I don't mind so much due to the swiftness of bootup. Also, THANK YOU.
